		<div id="comment_body_65243085"><p>It's actually long been held by economists that propping up failing industries merely puts money in the pockets of shareholders who don't want to invest. See how the YS car industry fared against Japan after using tariffs to keep them out for a while. Japan just kept innovating while the US kept paying dividends, eventually leading to the loss of a large part of the US carmakers.</p><p>Cheap labour is a crutch for non-performing capitalists. This argument has also been made many times by trade unions. If you reall<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_65243085">

</div>
</div>

